<!-- templates/budget-planner/starting-point.hbs -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
  <style>
    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 12mm;
    }

    body {
      font-family: {{customization.fontFamily}};
      color: #333;
      line-height: 1.4;
    }

    .header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      border-bottom: 3px solid {{customization.primaryColor}};
      padding-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .title {
      font-size: 26px;
      color: {{customization.primaryColor}};
      margin-bottom: 5px;
    }

    .subtitle {
      font-size: 12px;
      color: #666;
    }

    .intro {
      background: #f8f9fa;
      padding: 12px 15px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      font-size: 12px;
      color: #555;
    }

    .section {
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    .section-title {
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: {{customization.primaryColor}};
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
    }

    .icon {
      font-size: 16px;
    }

    .input-row {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 8px 12px;
      background: white;
      border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
      border-radius: 6px;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }

    .input-label {
      font-size: 12px;
      color: #444;
    }

    .input-value {
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: {{customization.primaryColor}};
      min-width: 100px;
      text-align: right;
      border-bottom: 2px dotted #ccc;
    }

    .calculation-box {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, {{customization.primaryColor}}10, {{customization.secondaryColor}}10);
      border: 2px solid {{customization.primaryColor}};
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 15px;
      margin-top: 15px;
    }

    .calc-title {
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: {{customization.primaryColor}};
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    .calc-row {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 6px 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
    }

    .calc-row:last-child {
      border-bottom: none;
      padding-top: 10px;
      margin-top: 6px;
      border-top: 2px solid {{customization.primaryColor}};
    }

    .calc-label {
      font-size: 12px;
    }

    .calc-value {
      font-size: 16px;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: {{customization.primaryColor}};
      min-width: 100px;
      text-align: right;
      border-bottom: 2px dotted #ccc;
    }

    .result-value {
      font-size: 18px;
      color: {{customization.primaryColor}};
    }

    .note {
      margin-top: 15px;
      padding: 10px 12px;
      background: #fff3cd;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-size: 11px;
      color: #856404;
    }

    .note-title {
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-bottom: 3px;
    }

    .date-box {
      margin-top: 12px;
      text-align: right;
      font-size: 12px;
      color: #666;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="header">
    <h1 class="title">Your Financial Starting Point</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Complete this page before you begin ‚Äî it's your baseline for measuring progress</p>
  </div>

  <div class="intro">
    <strong>Why this matters:</strong> You can't improve what you don't measure. Take 10 minutes to fill this out honestly.
    Come back to this page in December to see how far you've come!
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title"><span class="icon">üíµ</span> Monthly Income (after taxes)</div>
    <div class="input-row">
      <span class="input-label">Primary job / salary</span>
      <span class="input-value">$ _______</span>
    </div>
    <div class="input-row">
      <span class="input-label">Side income / freelance</span>
      <span class="input-value">$ _______</span>
    </div>
    <div class="input-row">
      <span class="input-label">Other income</span>
      <span class="input-value">$ _______</span>
    </div>
    <div class="input-row" style="background: #f0f0f0;">
      <span class="input-label"><strong>TOTAL MONTHLY INCOME</strong></span>
      <span class="input-value">$ _______</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title"><span class="icon">üè†</span> Monthly Fixed Expenses</div>
    <div class="input-row">
      <span class="input-label">Rent / Mortgage</span>
      <span class="input-value">$ _______</span>
    </div>
    <div class="input-row">
      <span class="input-label">Utilities (electric, water, gas, internet)</span>
      <span class="input-value">$ _______</span>
    </div>
    <div class="input-row">
      <span class="input-label">Transportation (car payment, insurance, gas)</span>
      <span class="input-value">$ _______</span>
    </div>
    <div class="input-row">
      <span class="input-label">Insurance (health, life, etc.)</span>
      <span class="input-value">$ _______</span>
    </div>
    <div class="input-row">
      <span class="input-label">Subscriptions & memberships</span>
      <span class="input-value">$ _______</span>
    </div>
    <div class="input-row" style="background: #f0f0f0;">
      <span class="input-label"><strong>TOTAL FIXED EXPENSES</strong></span>
      <span class="input-value">$ _______</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="calculation-box">
    <div class="calc-title">üìä Your Net Worth Snapshot</div>
    <div class="calc-row">
      <span class="calc-label">Total Savings (all accounts)</span>
      <span class="calc-value">$ _______</span>
    </div>
    <div class="calc-row">
      <span class="calc-label">Total Debt (credit cards, loans, etc.)</span>
      <span class="calc-value">$ _______</span>
    </div>
    <div class="calc-row">
      <span class="calc-label"><strong>NET WORTH</strong> (Savings - Debt)</span>
      <span class="calc-value result-value">$ _______</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="note">
    <div class="note-title">üí° Don't worry if your net worth is negative!</div>
    Many people start there. What matters is the direction you're heading.
    This number will improve as you follow your budget and pay down debt.
  </div>

  <div class="date-box">
    Date completed: ____/____/{{year}}
  </div>
</body>

</html>
